.SH "NAME"
rcb-delete \- delete files into rcb
.SH "SYNOPSIS"
.sp
\fBrcb delete\fP [\fIoptions\fP] [\fIarguments\fP]
.br
\fBrcb delete\fP [\fIarguments\fP] [\fIoptions\fP]
.br
\fBrcb delete\fP [\fIoptions\fP]
.br
\fBrcb delete\fP [\fIarguments\fP]
.br
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
.sp
The delete command allows for file deletion. Upon use it will save essential details into \fI.rcb/data/rcb.sqlite3\fP about the file before moving it into the \fI.rcb/file/\fP directory. If an existing file entry is found with the same filename it will automatically increment it with a number to prevent filename collisions before moving.
.SH "DELETE OPTIONS"
.sp
\fBdelete\fP \fI<filename>\fP
.br
.sp
Delete file(s) by filename
.sp
\fB\-\-\fP
.br
.sp
Options end after this point.
.sp
\fB\-\-help\fP, \fB\-h\fP
.br
.sp
Prints basic usage of rcb delete.
.sp
\fB\-\-verbose\fP, \fB\-v\fP
.br
.sp
Provides verbose information to console.
.sp
\fB\-\-silent\fP, \fB\-s\fP
.br
.sp
Silences output to console.
.sp
\fB\-\-force\fP, \fB\-f\fP
.br
.sp
Forces file deletion.
.sp
\fB\-\-no\-directorysize\fP
.br
.sp
Don\(cqt save size for filetype of directory.
